## ğŸš‚ Deploy to Railway

### Method 1: GitHub (Recommended)

1. Push this folder to a GitHub repo
1. Go to [railway.app](https://railway.app) â†’ New Project
1. Select â€œDeploy from GitHub repoâ€
1. Choose your repo
1. Add environment variables (from `.env.example`)
1. Click Deploy âœ…

### Method 2: Railway CLI

```bash
npm install -g @railway/cli
railway login
railway init
railway up
```

### Setting Environment Variables on Railway

In your Railway project â†’ Settings â†’ Variables, add:

```
BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token
API_ID=your_api_id
API_HASH=your_api_hash
OWNER_ID=your_telegram_id
OWNER_USERNAME=your_username
DATABASE_URL=  â† Railway auto-fills this if you add PostgreSQL plugin
```

### Add PostgreSQL on Railway

1. In your project â†’ New â†’ Database â†’ PostgreSQL
1. Railway automatically sets `DATABASE_URL` â€” no manual config needed

